<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>Nature</title>

    <!-- Internal CSS -->
    <style>
        body {
            background-color: lightgreen;
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
        }

        h1 {
            color: darkgreen;
            text-align: center;
        }

        h2 {
            color: green;
        }

        p {
            color: black;
        }

        .content {
            background-color: white;
            padding: 20px;
            margin: 20px;
        }

        a {
            color: blue;
            text-decoration: none;
        }

        a:hover {
            color: red;
        }

        table {
            width: 70%;
            border-collapse: collapse;
            margin-top: 10px;
        }

        th {
            background-color: green;
            color: white;
        }

        th, td {
            border: 1px solid black;
            padding: 8px;
            text-align: center;
        }
    </style>
</head>

<body>

    <h1>Nature</h1>

    <div class="content">

        <h2>Introduction</h2>
        <p>
            Nature is the most beautiful gift on Earth. It includes trees,
            rivers, mountains, animals, and plants.
        </p>

        <h2>Importance of Nature</h2>
        <p>
            Nature provides us with fresh air, water, food, and shelter.
            It helps maintain balance in the environment.
        </p>

        <h2>Benefits of Nature (Unordered List)</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Fresh Air</li>
            <li>Clean Water</li>
            <li>Healthy Environment</li>
            <li>Food Resources</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Ways to Protect Nature (Ordered List)</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>Plant More Trees</li>
            <li>Reduce Pollution</li>
            <li>Save Water</li>
            <li>Recycle Waste Materials</li>
        </ol>

        <h2>Nature Resources Table</h2>

        <table>
            <tr>
                <th>Resource</th>
                <th>Use</th>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Trees</td>
                <td>Provide Oxygen</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Rivers</td>
                <td>Provide Water</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Soil</td>
                <td>Grow Crops</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Forests</td>
                <td>Home for Animals</td>
            </tr>
        </table>

        <h2>Inline CSS Example</h2>

        <p style="color: blue; font-size: 20px;">
            This paragraph uses inline CSS to change the text color and font size.
        </p>

        <h2>Internal CSS Example</h2>

        <p>
            The background color of this webpage is set to light green using
            Internal CSS. The CSS code is written inside the style tag in the
            head section of the HTML document.
        </p>

        <h2>Conclusion</h2>

        <p>
            We should protect nature and keep our surroundings clean for a
            healthy future.
        </p>

        <h2>Learn More</h2>

        <p>
            <a href="https://www.wikipedia.org" target="_blank">
                Click Here to Learn More About Nature
            </a>
        </p>

    </div>

</body>
</html>
